with chocolate sauce and sprinkled with nuts.<br>- Replace cardamom with cinnamon or other spices as desired.<br>- Instead of shop-bought flaked almonds, prepare your own nuts: before starting the recipe preheat oven to 160°C, spread whole nuts (e.g. almonds, pistachios, pecans) in a single layer on a baking tray and toast for <b>10 minutes.<b> Once cooled, place nuts into mixing bowl and chop <b><strong>5-10 sec\/speed 5<\/strong><b> and sprinkle over pears."],"basicInfo":["easy","10m","40m","4 portions"]}